🧠 2) DSA — LONGEST SUBSTRING (WITHOUT REPEATING CHARACTERS)
🔹 Problem Understanding
Find the length of longest substring without repeating characters
Sliding window pattern + HashSet / dictionary
Example Implementation
def longest_substring(s):
    char_index = {}
    left = 0
    max_len = 0

    for right, c in enumerate(s):
        if c in char_index and char_index[c] >= left:
            left = char_index[c] + 1
        char_index[c] = right
        max_len = max(max_len, right - left + 1)

    return max_len
Time: O(n)
Space: O(min(n, charset_size))
Variations (Real-Time)
Longest substring with at most K distinct characters
Longest substring with exactly N vowels
Streaming input → maintain window for last N characters
GS Interview Angle
